    "answer": "AE",
    "explanation": "【핵심 용어】\n▸ VPC Lambda — ENI(Elastic Network Interface) 생성으로 VPC 리소스 접근\n▸ 보안 그룹 규칙 — 양방향 트래픽 확인 필수(아웃바운드 + 인바운드)\n▸ EC2 권한 — Lambda가 VPC 모드에서 ENI 관리 권한 필요\n\n【정답 포인트】\n(A) 네트워크 연결성 — Lambda(아웃바운드) → DB(인바운드) 양방향 확인\n▸ Lambda 보안 그룹: 포트 1433 아웃바운드 허용\n▸ DB 보안 그룹: Lambda SG에서 포트 1433 인바운드 허용\n(E) VPC Lambda의 필수 IAM 권한\n▸ ec2:CreateNetworkInterface — ENI 생성\n▸ ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaces — ENI 조회\n▸ ec2:DeleteNetworkInterface — ENI 삭제\n\n【오답 체크】\n(B) 방향 반대(Lambda의 인바운드, DB의 아웃바운드는 불필요)\n(C) NAT 게이트웨이와 퍼블릭 액세스는 같은 VPC 내 통신에 불필요\n(D) RDS API 권한이 아닌 네트워크 인터페이스 관리 권한이 필요\n\n【시험 포인트】\n VPC Lambda의 두 가지 문제 진단: (1) 네트워크 경로(보안 그룹), (2) IAM 권한(EC2 ENI 관리). 둘 다 필수적으로 확인해야 함.",
    "en_q": "A developer needs to troubleshoot an AWS Lambda function in a development environment. The Lambda function is configured in VPC mode and needs to connect to an existing Amazon RDS for SQL Server DB instance. The DB instance is deployed in a private subnet and accepts connections by using port 1433. When the developer tests the function, the function reports an error when it tries to connect to the database. Which combination of steps should the developer take to diagnose this issue? (Choose two.)",
    "en_opts": {
      "A": "Check that the function's security group has outbound access on port 1433 to the DB instance's security group. Check that the DB instance's security group has inbound access on port 1433 from the function's security group.",
      "B": "Check that the function's security group has inbound access on port 1433 from the DB instance's security group. Check that the DB instance's security group has outbound access on port 1433 to the function's security group.",
      "C": "Check that the VPC is set up for a NAT gateway. Check that the DB instance has the public access option turned on.",
      "D": "Check that the function's execution role permissions include rds:DescribeDBInstances, rds:ModifyDBInstance. and rds:DescribeDBSecurityGroups for the DB instance.",
      "E": "Check that the function's execution role permissions include ec2:CreateNetworkInterface, ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaces, and ec2:DeleteNetworkInterface."
    },
    "source": "https://www.examtopics.com/discussions/amazon/view/124780-exam-aws-certified-developer-associate-dva-c02-topic-1/"
